1.   Something that is built, as for human habitation; a structure. 2.   The act, process, art, or occupation of constructing. 1.   (Building) something built with a roof and walls, such as a house or factory 2.   (Building) the act, business, occupation, or art of building houses, boats, etc    1.   any relatively permanent enclosed structure on a plot of land, having a roof and usu. windows.     2.   anything built or constructed.     3.   the act, business, or practice of constructing houses, office buildings, etc. 